00:07:17.100 --> 00:07:21.260
identity transformer is the normal thing that Glue does. And it basically says find this

00:07:21.260 --> 00:07:27.660
variable and replace it with its value. Epoxy steps in here and uses the transformer argument

00:07:27.660 --> 00:07:33.859
to provide its own logic for what should happen when we see these embraced expressions. And

00:07:33.859 --> 00:07:40.140
that lets us do things like use the dot dollar syntax. And now we have a number formatted

